## When Building Custom Is the Right Decision

A unified platform is not the right answer for every organization. Custom builds are the correct choice when specific conditions apply:

* Proprietary ML Research: If your team is training foundation models from scratch on domain-specific data, not just implementing retrieval on top of existing language models, you need custom infrastructure.
* Regulatory Mandates for On-Premise Deployment: Some jurisdictions or high-security industries require that all data processing occurs on physical infrastructure the organization controls without cloud vendor involvement. 
* Extreme Conversation Volume: At extremely high volumes, running millions of complex queries per month, self-managed infrastructure economics might begin to make more sense than SaaS platform limits.

For companies where none of these conditions apply, spending months of engineering hours maintaining a custom AI chatbot drains resources from your main product.

## The Middle Ground: Platform Core with API Extensibility

The build versus buy framing implies a strict binary choice, but enterprise deployments rarely fit neatly into one category. Chatzy AI operates as a comprehensive AI operating system, providing extensive API access for teams that need to go beyond standard configurations.

You can rely on the platform for knowledge management, omnichannel routing, and analytics. Then, handle custom internal tool connections through our structured API flow. This architecture delivers platform speed without sacrificing technical control where it truly matters. You can build advanced internal workflows using our [developer API capabilities](https://chatzy.ai/api-access).

