## FAQ

### Can Chatzy AI connect to our proprietary systems?
Yes. Chatzy AI offers extensive API access and extensibility. Developers can integrate the platform into custom workflows and connect external systems via tailored API configurations, ensuring it works seamlessly with your proprietary tools.

### What happens if we need to change underlying AI models?
Chatzy AI offers a flexible multi-model architecture. You can choose or bring your own AI models, such as OpenAI, Claude, or Gemini. This gives you full flexibility over performance tuning, allowing you to switch models based on tasks without rebuilding your infrastructure.

### Does the platform support complex business workflows?
Yes. Chatzy AI utilizes the concept of AI agent squads, where multiple specialized agents collaborate to handle complex workflows. Tasks can be dynamically routed between support, sales, and escalation agents.

### Is the AI capable of voice interactions?
Absolutely. Beyond text-based chat, Chatzy AI includes advanced voice AI agents capable of handling inbound and outbound calls at scale, supporting thousands of concurrent conversations and near-instant handoffs.

### How secure is Chatzy AI for enterprise data?
Chatzy AI positions itself as an enterprise-grade platform. It features JWT-based authentication, GDPR compliance, ISO 27001 certification, SOC 2 compliance, and PCI-DSS standards, making it highly secure for handling sensitive data.

### Can custom integrations be built on top of Chatzy AI?
Yes. For advanced use cases, developers can utilize full API access to craft custom endpoints, automate internal processes, and build tailored analytics solutions alongside the built-in monitoring tools.

